{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e269503c-7cda-4c3c-a41d-2da1bf399300","content":"No files found in the workspace. Since there's no existing file to edit, here's exactly what you need to do:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the namespace for your ViewModel and set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nReplace `YourApp.ViewModels` / `YourApp.Views` with your actual namespaces.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat broken bindings as build errors instead of silent runtime failures -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler resolves bindings against `SettingsViewModel` at compile time. If you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you'll get a **build error** like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`x:DataType`** enables compiled bindings — the compiler validates property names/types and generates direct property access (faster, no reflection).\n- You can set `x:DataType` on any element, not just the root — useful when a `DataTemplate` binds to a different type.\n- If you need a **runtime binding** somewhere (e.g., `RelativeSource`), opt out locally with `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"603c5122-8aea-42bc-80b8-376e950f1026","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking about a file they have but it's not in the current working directory. Let me check what's in the current directory.","outputTokens":735,"requestId":"B7D0:2A1B2F:130ACA:18C5E2:69FFD77B"},"id":"5b112282-c8e5-4015-bdbd-9a46642ea1c7","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:55:38.028Z","parentId":"a223e2ce-a65e-4623-b804-57499b34cd6c"}
